                            <comment id="17814838" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 6 Feb 2024 14:30:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at the SVG, there is an invisible &quot;lvl-0&quot; graph node circle on the far left side, with invisible lines to the collections. Also, there is a fixed 100px padding to the left of the entire graph, pushing the rest of the graph to the right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this some limitation of the graph component we use, that there needs to be a level-0 node? If so, could we compress it to take less horizontal space?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13066520/13066520_Skjermbilde+2024-02-06+kl.+15.27.24.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17814973" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 6 Feb 2024 19:25:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The PR fixes these issues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Take hostname width into account when positioning graph in SVG canvas&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Reduce left-pad 100px to 10px&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Auto refresh graph when resizing window&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://youtu.be/F_0Nab8Ylow&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;video for a demo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
